Two small shipping companies reacheda pay deal with striking seamen late yesterday, but unionleaders said most of Brazil's 40,000 seamen were still onstrike.    A union spokesman in Rio de Janeiro said the seamen hadaccepted a 120 pct pay raise offer from the companies, Globoand Flumar, which have less than 200 employees each.    The two-week strike comes as Brazil faces a debt crisis andis delaying exports badly needed to earn foreign exchange.    Labour Minister Almir Pazzionotto said the government willnot force a settlement of the strike, which was ruled illegallast Friday. Reuter&#3;